{
  "stem": "11174.3",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they were hollering and cursing and-- And then one thing, there was a guy with us-- his name was Frankel, from Limanowa-- who his things with him was like this cane.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He walked with a cane type of a valise.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He had all his stuff there.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Somehow, this was like a thorn in the German eyes-- the German's eyes, that he probably has a machine gun there in that.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "There were other valises they weren't-- when they saw this, we had to stop and they had to open up.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So once we were stopped with him.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they opened up, and they carried on.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They were tallit and teffilin.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They ripped the tallit and threw the teffilin.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And cursing, you dirty Churchill, you dirty-- Roosevelt they called Rosenfeld.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The Jewish Rosenfeld, president.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And cursed, aus Palestine, aus-- there would be no more Palestine.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Cursed.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And finally, then pack yourself around back.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So we-- so we packed.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "While packing, they started to run, they shot at us.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But they didn't shoot to-- to kill, just to make us more frightened.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "The fear there is-- you know-- German army shoots at you, you know?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "On one of the trucks, a soldier was there.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "He had a chop-- chop knife, to chop meat, you know?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "So he showed us, and said in German, this is what we're going to chop up all the Jews.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "This is-- So we went back, in other words, not continuing forward, but backwards.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "We're going back home to one little town.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "The name was Nisko.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Who did you meet there?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Pardon me?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But, in Nisko we went-- we came in-- yeah.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Before that little town, I begged the few people that we were together, have a heart, the [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
